'''Air Jordan''' was an airline based in [[Jordan]]. It was founded in 1950.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Kassem |first1=M. Sami |title=Strategic Management of Services in the Arab Gulf States: Company and Industry Cases |isbn=3110854015 |page=136}}</ref> In 1958, it acquired [[Arab Airways Jerusalem]] and changed its name to '''Air Jordan of the Holy Land'''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Arab Airways (Jerusalem) history from Jordan, Rest of World |url=https://airlinehistory.co.uk/airline/arab-airways-jerusalem/ |website=Airline History}}</ref> It ceased operating in 1961.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Davies |first1=Ronald Edward George |title=A history of the world's airlines |date=1964 |isbn=0192159283|quote=Air Jordan ceased operation on 1 September 1961, its place being taken by Jordan Airways}}</ref>
The airline was owned by American and Jordanian business interests.<ref>{{cite web |title=World survey of civil aviation. Near and Middle East |url=https://archive.org/stream/worldsurveyofci00unit/worldsurveyofci00unit_djvu.txt |website=Internet Archive |publisher=Washington, D.C. : U.S. Dept. of Commerce, Business and Defense Services Administration |date=1961}}</ref>
