'''Jean-Pierre Berçot''' was the [[France|French]] [[Ambassador (diplomacy)|ambassador]] to [[Chad]] until November 2006. On 1 August 2004, he said that France would deploy 200 [[soldier]]s to help secure Chad's eastern [[border]] with [[Sudan]]'s conflict-torn [[Darfur]] region.<ref>"French army moves to Sudan border: France is deploying 200 soldiers to help secure Chad's eastern border with Sudan's conflict-torn Darfur region".  http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/3943137.stm</ref> He was [[Prefect of Saint Pierre and Miquelon|prefect]] of [[Saint-Pierre and Miquelon]].<ref>[[:fr:Liste des préfets de Saint-Pierre-et-Miquelon]]</ref>

